{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fd56c2cf-6216-45e5-9798-3ae3624889fc","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the TFM:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter editing, run `dotnet restore && dotnet build` to verify everything compiles. Check the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for any breaking API changes relevant to your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9d7a3dd2-8326-4b39-a445-711914e1237a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search files since they described what they have.","outputTokens":271,"requestId":"A444:FFF68:233EA2C:26FB372:6A03D924"},"id":"9ef93b00-57ec-4e34-a5c3-380330c38fe0","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:51:38.226Z","parentId":"f10020c8-0df1-4846-97b5-a996467e51ca"}
